Build succeeded. The `UserActivityTracker` component is ready. Here's how to use it:

```razor
<UserActivityTracker TimeoutSeconds="120" OnIdle="HandleIdle" OnActive="HandleActive">
    <p>Your app content here...</p>
</UserActivityTracker>

@code {
    private Task HandleIdle() { /* e.g., show warning */ return Task.CompletedTask; }
    private Task HandleActive() { /* e.g., dismiss warning */ return Task.CompletedTask; }
}
```

**How it works:**
- A collocated JS module listens for `mousemove`, `keydown`, `click`, `scroll`, and `touchstart` on `document`
- A timeout resets on each event; when it expires, `OnIdle` fires
- Any subsequent activity fires `OnActive` and restarts the timer
- `IAsyncDisposable` ensures the JS module cleans up all listeners and timers on removal
